author: Life Noggin
description:
If just one major impact happens in Earth’s orbit, thousands of high-speed fragments can turn space into a dangerous debris field. GPS collapses, networks fail, and global transportation grinds to a halt. And the worst part is that scientists warn that we may be closer to this tipping point than most people realize.
